# Java Deploy parity traps

Lessons from SignupSheet / DirtBowl Deploy work. Apply whenever changing `designer-web/server/*ToXml*`, Preview/runtime, or Tomcat CSS.

## 1. Design canvas ≫ Preview ≫ do not unify for Deploy

Fix Deploy/Preview in **server export or runtime** paths. Do not rewrite Design `*CanvasRow` idle/edit UX so “Preview matches Design.” See `tawala-work-scopes.mdc`.

## 2. Java XML factories are strict (silent empty output)

Legacy Java drops unknown or illegal nesting — often as blank pages, not stack traces:

| Trap | Do instead |
|------|------------|
| Wrap Document body in `<division>` | Paragraphs only; Document has no division |
| Nest `<font><font>…` | One font level; put b/i/u **inside** font |
| Document field `<<Form:Field>>` | `Record:Form:Field` (or project’s Record token form) |

When Deploy looks empty, check Tomcat logs for `No class registered for …` before blaming CSS.

## 3. FIB prompt: three contracts, three parsers

- **Design** may keep underscores / rich HTML while editing.
- **Preview** (`fibPrompt.mjs`) and **Deploy** (`fibToXml.mjs` / `fibRichPromptToXml.mjs`) must both turn `_` runs into blanks.
- Contenteditable wraps (`</span>`) contain `/` — **never** take the legacy `Label/` slash path on raw HTML; underscore-match on **plain** text first.
- Freeform: one Design soft-row (`<br>` / line) → **one** Deploy `<paragraph>` (multi-blank lines stay one line).
- Character formatting on labels: mirror Design B/I/U (and face/size/color) into Deploy font XML — do not strip to plain and re-guess bold from the word “Name”.

Add/extend unit tests on **each path you touch** (`fibPrompt`, `fibToXml`, Document HTML→XML).

## 4. Process timing vs “latest submission”

Java runs Process **before** persisting the current form submission. A Document MQL shown after Submit can be **one record behind**. Stock Signup puts the list on the **Form** (or refresh after Thank-you). Do not “fix” empty tables by changing Design layout unless the owner wants that product pattern.

## 5. Ops before code archaeology

- Vite `:5173` often survives while Express `:3001` dies → Preview/Deploy “failed to fetch”. Check `/api/health`; use `designer-web/scripts/ensure-dev-api.sh`.
- Java Deploy credentials default **`dev` / `dev`**.
- Stale Preview sessions or Tomcat `submission` rows look like product bugs — clear or Redeploy with a fresh unique id before deep debugging.
- Theme/validation CSS under `docker/tomcat/css/project/` may need hard refresh / cache-buster after `docker cp`.

## 6. Misleading deploy errors

Prefer accurate parse/deploy messages over generic copy (e.g. do not blame “itemization headers” for unrelated XML failures).
